('TypeError: Cannot read property ''description'' of null at ngOnInit', 'angular', 'HIGH', '[{"solution": "Check if object exists before accessing nested properties: if(this.feedbackdetails && this.feedbackdetails.description) or use optional chaining: this.feedbackdetails?.description", "percentage": 95}, {"solution": "Use hasOwnProperty check: if(this.feedbackdetails && this.feedbackdetails.hasOwnProperty(\"description\"))", "percentage": 85}]'::jsonb, 'Understanding null vs undefined in JavaScript, basic Angular component lifecycle', 'Component loads without errors, null check prevents property access errors', 'Attempting to access nested properties without checking parent object existence first, forgetting that JSON.parse returns null on parse failure', 0.92, 'haiku', NOW(), 'https://stackoverflow.com/questions/68440472/how-to-handle-null-case-in-angular', 'admin:1764191519'),

